{
  "local_port": 35222,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best Android app for listening to and downloading English songs with lyrics?",
  "response": "There are several great Android apps for listening to and downloading English songs with lyrics. Here are some of the best options:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Spotify**\n   - **Features**: Spotify offers a vast library of English songs with lyrics displayed in real-time. You can create playlists, download songs for offline listening, and discover new music.\n   - **Lyrics**: Lyrics are available for most songs through the dedicated lyrics feature.\n   - **Download**: Requires a Spotify Premium subscription for offline downloads.\n   - **Pros**: High-quality audio, personalized recommendations, and a massive music library.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Musixmatch**\n   - **Features**: Musixmatch is a dedicated lyrics app that syncs lyrics with songs playing on Spotify, YouTube, or other music apps. It also has a built-in music player.\n   - **Lyrics**: Real-time synchronized lyrics for millions of songs.\n   - **Download**: You can download lyrics and songs with a premium subscription.\n   - **Pros**: Excellent for lyric enthusiasts, integrates with other music apps.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Wynk Music**\n   - **Features**: Wynk is a popular music app that offers a wide range of English songs with lyrics. It also supports offline downloads.\n   - **Lyrics**: Lyrics are displayed for most songs.\n   - **Download**: Available with a subscription.\n   - **Pros**: Affordable plans and a good selection of music.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Gaana**\n   - **Features**: Gaana is an Indian music app with a large collection of English songs. It includes lyrics for many tracks.\n   - **Lyrics**: Lyrics are available for selected songs.\n   - **Download**: Requires a premium subscription for offline downloads.\n   - **Pros**: Great for multilingual users and Bollywood fans.\n\n---\n\n### **5. SoundCloud**\n   - **Features**: SoundCloud has a mix of mainstream and independent artists. Some songs come with lyrics in the description or comments.\n   - **Lyrics**: Not all songs have synchronized lyrics, but many user uploads include lyrics.\n   - **Download**: Offline listening is available with SoundCloud Go+.\n   - **Pros**: Ideal for discovering new and indie artists.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Audiomack**\n   - **Features**: Audiomack offers free music streaming and downloads for many songs, including English tracks.\n   - **Lyrics**: Lyrics are not always available, but some songs include them in the description.\n   - **Download**: Free downloads are available for select tracks.\n   - **Pros**: Completely free for many songs.\n\n---\n\n### **7. YouTube Music**\n   - **Features**: YouTube Music provides official songs, remixes, and covers. Lyrics are available for most songs.\n   - **Lyrics**: Real-time lyrics are displayed for many tracks.\n   - **Download**: Requires a YouTube Music Premium subscription for offline downloads.\n   - **Pros**: Access to a vast library of songs and videos.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Shazam**\n   - **Features**: Shazam is primarily a song identification app, but it also provides lyrics for identified songs.\n   - **Lyrics**: Lyrics are available for most identified tracks.\n   - **Download**: Doesn\u2019t directly download songs but links to streaming platforms.\n   - **Pros**: Great for discovering songs and accessing lyrics.\n\n---\n\n### **Recommendation**:\nIf you want a **comprehensive experience** with lyrics and downloads, **Spotify** or **Musixmatch** are excellent choices. For **free options**, consider **Audiomack** or **SoundCloud**. Choose based on your preferences for features, offline access, and cost!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
